It’s the final day of the year and I can’t help but feel grateful for all the collaborators and friends that I got to work with this year. 

Thank you to the directors, producers, production companies, brands and businesses that trusted me to shoot videos for them and bring their stories to life. 

One of the biggest lessons that I learned from this year was that sustainable change happens in 2 degree shifts. This was prevalent in my personal life with lack of attention to mental health and taking care of my physical body and heart. I think I often find myself wanting 180 degree shifts with my habits, career decisions, how much I’d like to make, clients I want to work with, but it’s really not sustainable long term because there’s no consistency. I have to remind myself that I’m in it for the long run and I got to pace myself and live a little. 

So this year it looked like simplifying my life, and putting more emphasis on fulfillment. I spent more time going on runs, playing more soccer, watching the World Cup, reconnecting with friends and family, and diving into yoga and meditation. The point of working hard is so that we get to create more time to spend with others and enrich our life with more experiences. Life goes by fast, I mean it’s already been close to 3 years since the pandemic started and life just keeps on going. I hope that you’re able to simplify and be able to squeeze the juice out of every day this new season. Happy new year!!! Cheers to the next one!!

Check out my updated cinematography reel(spliced in with some Steadicam operating).

Thank you to all collaborators from last year that trusted me to help with their projects. I look forward to working with you in this upcoming season!

If you’re an artist or business needing help with your projects, don’t hesitate to reach out! 
Thanks everyone!

🔦Lighting BTS on the Disney Jr commercial I recently got to be the cinematographer for - swipe for lighting setups😁

For the 1st scene(ice rink), Paul(the kindest and best gaffer in nashville with best team) was able to get two sky panels up with soft box going diff and through 1/4 grid silk(flagged on sides to control spill), hudson spider octo for additional overhead light, litepanel for a hair light, and a M40 to bring a shaft light towards where our talent was. 

For the 2nd scene, we had a similar lighting setup but had to bring in an additional Aputure 600C to bring light on talent/bring up levels in the room. We had aster tubes plus a light mat to have control over the color temp our “overhead” lights were casting. Overall, the goal for this spot was to make bright, cheery, and clean and feel happy with what we were able to achieve! Shot on Alexa mini+Cooke S4
